parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring can cause the tire to puncture or blow out, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
The failure of airbag deployment can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbag is designed to provide critical protection to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
broken windows due to metal pieces on the airbag cover
burns to the face from deploying airbags.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window system can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, and in some cases, may lead to safety issues if the window becomes stuck in a position that obstructs the driver's view.
symptoms: The power window does not roll down or up
the window gets stuck in a position
the window has to be pulled up or down manually
the window switch does not respond.
